==English==

===Etymology===
From the Bible account of the poor widow's donation to the temple contribution box. Found at [http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Bible_%28World_English%29/Mark#Chapter_12  Mark 12.38-44] and [http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Bible_%28World_English%29/Luke#Chapter_21  Luke 21.1-4]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A very small, [[gift]] or [[donation]] which, however, represents a great [[sacrifice]] on the part of the giver.
#(numismatics) Name given to the [[lepton]] coin.

